  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated COVID19 Response Programme for the Rohingya and Surrounding Host Communities_DSK</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hygiene practices will be improved through installation of 20 community-based handwashing points. Additionally, hygiene kits will be distributed to 300 households in the targeted area. Capacity building training on COVID-19 preparedness and response including IPC will be provided to frontline staff including Rohingya volunteers &amp; WaSH committee members with the aim of strengthening WaSH services at the community level.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased access to home-based health care services for the confirmed COVID-19 cases
 Increased knowledge of health facilities staff and CHW in home-based Covid 19 care

Reduced misbeliefs and spread of rumours about Covid 19 in the targeted area
Improved hygiene practices to prevent COVID-19 spread in Rohingya Refugee Camp</narrative>
  </description>
